  "body": "\nModules in `track-b-c-deferred/cherenkov/`:\n- `stages/ui_plan.py` \u2014 `UIElement`/`UISpec`/`UIScenario` Pydantic models.\n- `stages/ui_generate.py` \u2014 Playwright UI/E2E test generator (incl. `toHaveScreenshot` visual baselines).\n- `api/main.py`, `api/divergences.py` \u2014 an alternate FastAPI + WebSocket backend with a divergence corpus/action store.\n\n**Acceptance (post-gate):**\n- Decide per module: re-integrate vs **retire as superseded**. The supported review API already serves the dashboard, so `api/main.py`/`api/divergences.py` are likely **retire-and-delete** (document the decision) rather than re-integrate.\n- If UI-test generation is kept, fold `ui_plan`/`ui_generate` into the supported `cherenkov/stages/` with a smoke test and honest output (no fabricated success).\n- No new issue previously covered these \u2014 that is the gap this closes.",
